claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A flowchart depicting the selection and exclusion of study participants aged 18–64 years vaccinated over three influenza seasons (2018–2021), comparing those who received a recombinant vaccine (n ≈1,018,043 initially, 632,962 in final cohort) versus a standard-dose vaccine (n ≈1,758,235 initially, 997,366 in final cohort), with stepwise exclusions for nonmembers, inpatient vaccinations, outside date ranges, missing facility identifiers, and inability to assign propensity scores. The image is a participant flow diagram and does not present any data on antibody responses or immunogenicity; therefore, it does not support the claim. Note: The image quality is sufficient to confirm that no immunogenicity or antibody response data are shown.
